<template><div><h1 id="guide-to-town-of-host-enhanced-setting-up" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#guide-to-town-of-host-enhanced-setting-up"><span><font color=#f0b6d5>Guide to Town of Host: Enhanced - <font color=#ed543d>Setting Up</font></font></span></a></h1>
<p>Now that you’ve installed Town of Host: Enhanced, it's time to set up your experience, so let's do that!<br>
Don’t worry—this guide will walk you through every step, ensuring a smooth setup so you can jump straight into the action.</p>
<h3 id="step-1-set-your-game-settings" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-1-set-your-game-settings"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ed543d>Step 1:</font> Set your Game Settings</font></span></a></h3>
<p>These are the Vanilla Among Us settings, which can be customized if you wish. If you’re new to Town of Host: Enhanced (TOHE), it’s recommended to leave these settings as-is for a default TOHE gameplay experience. You can tweak things like player speed, vision, and task difficulty to personalize your game.</p>
<h3 id="step-2-set-your-system-settings" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-2-set-your-system-settings"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ed543d>Step 2:</font> Set your System Settings</font></span></a></h3>
<p>Here you can adjust System Settings to your preference. Most players leave these as the default settings until they’re more familiar with hosting games. These settings can affect aspects like how the mod behaves, performance, and certain special interactions during gameplay.</p>
<h3 id="step-3-select-your-gamemode" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-3-select-your-gamemode"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ed543d>Step 3:</font> Select your Gamemode</font></span></a></h3>
<p>TOHE offers several gamemodes, but in this guide, we’ll be covering the Standard TOHE gamemode. This mode is inspired by Town of Salem, a popular game that TOHE is based on. Other gamemodes may be explored later as needed, but for now, select Standard to stay aligned with the most common experience.</p>
<h3 id="step-4-set-your-mod-settings" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-4-set-your-mod-settings"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ed543d>Step 4:</font> Set your Mod Settings</font></span></a></h3>
<p>With your gamemode selected, it's time to configure Mod Settings. These settings let you customize specifics like:<br></p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Guesser Mode: A mode where players can guess other players' roles.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Map Selection: Choose how the maps are selected or even disable certain ones.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Devices/Tasks: You can enable or disable different tasks or modify the types of devices used in-game.<br></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Take your time with these settings, as they can drastically alter the gameplay experience. Once you're satisfied with your choices, move on to the next step.</p>
