<p>Now it’s time to choose your Roles! Each faction offers unique roles that define the gameplay:<br></p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Impostor Faction: Includes roles for the Impostor team.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Crewmate Faction: Includes roles for the Crewmate team.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Neutral Faction: Roles that don’t belong to either team, with their own set of goals.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Coven Faction: A third main team with its own unique objectives.<br></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Start with simpler roles that you’re familiar with, and then you can enable more complex roles as you get the hang of the game. If you're feeling adventurous, you can enable all roles, but be aware that this might be overwhelming for beginners.</p>
<h3 id="step-6-select-add-ons" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-6-select-add-ons"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ed543d>Step 6:</font> Select Add-Ons</font></span></a></h3>
<p>Add-Ons are additional modifiers that layer on top of roles and can add unique effects to the game. Some are exclusive to certain factions (like Impostors), while others are available to everyone. Browse through the available Add-Ons to find ones that you may like!<br></p>
<p>If you’re new, start with simpler Add-Ons (like Bait, Autopsy, etc) before diving into more complex ones.<br></p>
<p>Experiment with adding them after you’ve gotten familiar with the roles, or try them out together for a more dynamic experience.</p>
